        "title_GnwKjw": {
          "type": "title",
          "settings": {
            "title": "You don't need a biology degree to understand why BRAiNLUBE works. Here's the whole thing in plain English.",
            "heading_tag": "h2",
            "sm_size_multiplier": "sm-size--small",
            "sm_margin_top": 0,
            "size_multiplier": "size--default",
            "margin_top": 0
          }
        },
        "text_mnHHRQ": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Founder Steve Land is a computer engineer, not a chemist — so BRAiNLUBE got built the way he'd approach any hard technical problem: logically, and backed by research, not guesswork. That mindset is behind every ingredient on this page.</p><p>Most energy comes with a catch — caffeine wakes you up, but it also makes you jittery and anxious. So we didn't just throw in caffeine. We paired a moderate dose (130mg, about a strong coffee) with something called <strong>L-theanine</strong>, a natural compound found in tea. L-theanine takes the sharp, jittery edge off caffeine and turns it into smooth, steady focus. Think of caffeine as the gas pedal and L-theanine as the steering — together you go fast <em>and</em> stay in control. This combo is one of the most well-studied pairings in the focus world, and it's the heart of every can.<br/></p>",
            "sm_size_multiplier": "sm-size--default",
            "sm_margin_top": 0,
            "size_multiplier": "size--default",
            "margin_top": 0
          }
        }
      },
